@startuml context
!include cyber.puml
!include sprites/all.sprite
skinparam linetype ortho

title MedHub - System Context (C4 Level 1)

actor "Doctor" as Doctor
actor "Patient" as Patient
actor "Administrative\nPersonnel" as Admin
actor "System\nAdministrator" as SysAdmin

rectangle "MedHub\nWeb Application" as MedHub #lightblue

rectangle "Web Browser\n(Safari/Firefox/Chrome/Edge)" as Browser #lightgray
rectangle "SMTP / Email\nService" as SMTP #lightgray
rectangle "Object Storage\n(S3-compatible / MinIO)" as ObjStore #lightgray

Doctor --> Browser : uses
Patient --> Browser : uses
Admin --> Browser : uses
SysAdmin --> Browser : uses

Browser --> MedHub : HTTPS (TLS)\nREST/JSON, session cookie
MedHub --> SMTP : activation & appointment\nnotification emails (SR-033, SR-035)
MedHub --> ObjStore : store/fetch encrypted\nDICOM & report files (SR-013, SR-022)

note bottom of MedHub
  Single-tenant deployment per organization (ADR-0010).
  All PHI access passes the central AuthorizationService (SR-005).
end note

@enduml
